# README maintenance

[README.md](../../README.md) is the **public face** of Issues — the first doc visitors and agents read. Keep it accurate whenever user-visible capabilities or onboarding change.

## When to update README.md

| Trigger | Action in README |
|---------|------------------|
| New user-facing feature shipped | Add bullet under the correct **Features** subsection |
| Feature removed or renamed | Update or remove the matching bullet |
| Tech stack change (framework, DB, auth) | Update **Tech stack** table |
| Dev startup or URLs change | Update **Quick start** commands and links |
| New dev persona in `dev-import.sql` | Update dev login table |
| Project name or Sonar badges change | Update title and badge URLs |
| New top-level doc agents should know | Add row to **Documentation** table |

## What belongs in README vs other docs

| README | Elsewhere |
|--------|-----------|
| One-line pitch, tech stack, quick start | — |
| Feature bullets (what the product does) | [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) for routes, roles, click paths |
| Doc index links | Full detail in linked docs |
| Dev login table (summary) | Full personas in feature-catalog |

Do **not** duplicate route tables or API signatures in README — link to [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) and [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md).

## Feature bullet format

- Group under existing subsections (`Tickets & workflow`, `Projects & administration`, `Views & analytics`, `Notifications & email`, `Authentication`) or add a new subsection if needed.
- Start with **bold term** — short description.
- Use domain language from [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md).

## Finish checklist

Before marking a feature task **done** when behaviour is user-visible:

1. Update [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) (routes and steps).
2. Update README **Features** section (capability bullet).
3. Update [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) if vocabulary changed.

